      "acceptanceCriteria": "The relative hemolysis index (RH) is demonstrated to be a clinically relevant surrogate for pump-induced blood trauma and is directly linked to the COU decision criterion.",
      "rationale": "RH index is the accepted regulatory surrogate for pump-induced hemolysis per FDA guidance and ISO 10993-4. The COU decision criterion (RH < 1 relative to predicate device) directly maps to the clinical risk of hemolysis-related complications in CPB patients. QoI relevance is confirmed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
